# Parallel tool calls — OpenAI streams them at different `index` values so each
# has its own _ToolCallAggregator.  Tool 0 (index=0) is the racy one: id+args
# arrive before name. Tool 1 (index=1) is well-formed (id+name in first chunk).
#
# Both tools must emit a single ToolCallStartEvent with the correct name, in
# the order their START events fire — i.e. tool 1's START fires first because
# its name arrives in chunk 1; tool 0's START is delayed until chunk 2.
